## Design decisions
- Disabled models = unknown for routing/`is_known`; `include_disabled=True` for admin introspection
- Auto-enable providers only when request supplies keys/preset (not on every edit)
- Persist disabled_models failures raise → 500 to admin API
- Explicit Bearer/API-key headers beat session cookie (break-glass)
- `filter_chain` hard-empty (never fail-open past allowed/free constraints)
- Analytics SSE: admins `see_all`; users only own `user_id` traces
- Executor `_chain` always strips disabled + re-applies allowed/free after emergency heal
- Concurrent approve uses `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` + conditional UPDATE

## Lessons
- .cursorrules can be overwritten by concurrent agent sessions — re-read before editing, merge don't clobber
- App Platform does NOT support volumes — document ephemeral SQLite clearly
- Hatch force-include of missing static/dist breaks local installs — copy dist post-pip in Docker instead
- Colima must be started before docker build on this machine
- Spokenly MCP may be unavailable; supercoder says NEVER ASK — proceed autonomously
- FastAPI union StreamingResponse|JSONResponse needs response_model=None
- Project venv is `.venv` (uv), not `venv`
- Helpers existing ≠ wired — always verify call sites
- EventSource cannot send Authorization — use ?token= or session cookie for SSE
- CORS allow_credentials cannot pair with allow_origins=*
- Droplet compose publishes host port 80 (not 8080); data survives rebuilds via `nimmakai-data` volume
- DO User data embeds secrets (visible via metadata/API) — gitignore generated scripts; warn to rotate
- `_filter_available` must never fail-open to disabled models (empty → [])
- Seeded `api_keys_env` can block env aliases — `resolved_keys` must check alias envs
- Session auth must gate on account status the same as API keys
- EventBus subscriber filter: store `(see_all, user_id)` — `user_id=None` alone must not mean see-all
- KeyPool exposes `__len__`, not `.size`
- `esc()` does not make data safe inside JS string literals — use data attributes + addEventListener
- SQLite `isolation_level=None` needs explicit `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` for atomic multi-statement approves
